   "Per-stock probability is empirical-Bayes shrunk (k=25) toward the pattern rate \u2014 thin samples cannot fake conviction",
   "Confluence (>=2 patterns firing) is measured as its own historical series; otherwise the basis is the deepest per-stock history \u2014 chosen ex-ante by sample size, never by outcome (no winner's curse)",
   "Net EV = expectation minus the 0.4% IDX round-trip cost \u2014 an edge that dies to costs is SKIP",
   "EXECUTE requires net EV >= 5bp AND P >= 1.15x the base rate AND >=30 historical occurrences",
   "Suggested size = quarter-Kelly on the two-outcome bet, capped at 5% of book \u2014 a research hint, never advice",
   "Decay guard: once forward evidence (>=30 samples over >=10 distinct days) runs below 90% of the backtest estimate, EXECUTE demotes to WAIT",
   "Stocks tied to OJK manipulation cases (public record) = hard SKIP \u2014 a statistical edge on a manipulated stock is the pump itself"
